function retryRequest(request, retries) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    request().then(resolve).catch((error) => {
      if (retries > 0) {
        retryRequest(request, retries - 1).then(resolve).catch(reject);
      } else {
        reject(error);
      }
    });
  });
}
```

This function takes two arguments: `request` is a function that makes the request, and `retries` is the number of times to retry the request.

The function returns a new Promise that resolves with the result of the request, or rejects with an error if the request fails after all retries have been exhausted.

